WEBVTT

00:04.352 --> 00:11.359
♪

00:19.802 --> 00:26.809
♪

00:37.167 --> 00:40.431
- Yes!
- Yeah, come on!

00:40.475 --> 00:43.652
- Yeah. Trust me.

00:46.133 --> 00:47.308
- Welcome back.

00:48.918 --> 00:51.877
[metal detector whirring
and clicking]

00:51.921 --> 00:58.841
♪

00:58.884 --> 01:00.016
- Hey, you better
wait in line.

01:00.060 --> 01:01.583
We're all trying to get in.

01:08.198 --> 01:13.943
♪

01:13.986 --> 01:16.032
- Just stay close, Penny.

01:19.209 --> 01:21.907
♪

01:21.951 --> 01:23.735
- Whoa, whoa.
Easy there.

01:23.779 --> 01:26.347
My name's Pete.
Welcome.

01:26.390 --> 01:29.132
Penelope, right?
- Yeah, yeah.

01:29.176 --> 01:30.960
- Told you I'd be back.

01:31.003 --> 01:33.397
♪

01:33.441 --> 01:35.007
- Glad to see you got this guy
back here in one piece.

01:35.051 --> 01:36.270
- Pete, get over here.

01:36.313 --> 01:38.576
You gotta hear this.
- Hold on.

01:38.620 --> 01:41.884
♪

01:51.981 --> 01:54.201
- How close do you think
that was?

01:54.244 --> 01:55.767
- Don't worry.

01:55.811 --> 01:58.118
Hey...you're safe.

02:00.903 --> 02:01.860
Where you going?

02:01.904 --> 02:03.210
- Bathroom.

02:04.385 --> 02:06.822
- Well, should I--
- Think I can handle it.

02:08.737 --> 02:12.044
- She's on edge.
- Yeah, no shit.

02:12.088 --> 02:13.220
- Jesus, okay.

02:13.263 --> 02:15.047
- No--

02:16.962 --> 02:21.053
I'm sorry. I didn't--
I didn't mean to snap. I--

02:22.229 --> 02:24.318
This night has been
a long one.

02:24.361 --> 02:27.538
- Trust me. I know.

02:30.585 --> 02:35.546
♪

02:35.590 --> 02:37.853
- Like I said, I'm--I'm sorry.

02:39.028 --> 02:41.509
I can't imagine what
you're going through.

02:44.729 --> 02:47.297
You did what you had to do.
- I know.

02:59.266 --> 03:01.181
- Well,
tonight's almost over.

03:03.313 --> 03:05.097
- Gotta be honest.

03:07.230 --> 03:09.841
Not feeling great
about tomorrow either.

03:13.410 --> 03:15.673
I don't even know
where to begin.

03:15.717 --> 03:18.459
- Maybe you start
with firing the help.

03:18.502 --> 03:22.680
♪

03:25.683 --> 03:28.512
- I think I'm--I'm gonna
head upstairs.

03:31.385 --> 03:36.085
- Hey, I, uh, was gonna make--

03:36.128 --> 03:39.915
I don't know--a sandwich
or something for Jen.

03:39.958 --> 03:41.351
You want one?

03:43.135 --> 03:44.659
- Sure.

03:44.702 --> 03:46.313
Why not?

03:46.356 --> 03:47.357
- Cool.

03:47.401 --> 03:49.359
- Thanks.

03:49.403 --> 03:56.366
♪

03:58.281 --> 04:05.245
♪

04:11.468 --> 04:15.559
[elegant music
playing faintly]

04:17.996 --> 04:19.650
You're gonna be there
for me, right?

04:19.694 --> 04:23.175
- Of course.

04:23.219 --> 04:24.786
- I can't believe
I'm doing this.

04:26.744 --> 04:30.008
- Listen to your own voice
and what's in your heart.

04:36.145 --> 04:37.277
- There she is.

04:39.540 --> 04:41.759
How's my angel?

04:47.069 --> 04:49.158
You know what that is?

04:49.201 --> 04:51.900
I gave that to your mother
on our 20th anniversary.

04:51.943 --> 04:54.468
- Something old.
Something borrowed.

04:54.511 --> 04:57.862
- And something new.
- Something blue.

05:02.040 --> 05:04.695
- Maybe--maybe this is--
this is too fast.

05:04.739 --> 05:06.523
Maybe--maybe I should wait
a few more years.

05:06.567 --> 05:08.395
- A little cold feet
is normal.

05:08.438 --> 05:10.310
This is a big day for you.

05:10.353 --> 05:12.442
- For our whole family.

05:12.486 --> 05:15.619
- No, no.
I-I can't go through with this.

05:15.663 --> 05:17.055
- Sweetie,

05:17.099 --> 05:18.274
you're just overthinking it.

05:18.318 --> 05:19.536
- No, I'm not
overthinking it.

05:19.580 --> 05:20.798
I-I'm not leaving this room.

05:20.842 --> 05:22.060
I don't care what
they think of me.

05:22.104 --> 05:24.149
- Honey, your father is right.

05:24.193 --> 05:26.413
You are overthinking it. This--
- No, stop.

05:26.456 --> 05:28.415
I made my decision.

05:28.458 --> 05:30.504
Fine.

06:19.466 --> 06:22.077
- He hasn't come in yet!

06:22.120 --> 06:24.079
[metal detector whirring
and clicking]

06:30.085 --> 06:32.914
- I wish you would've
told me about Rex--

06:32.957 --> 06:36.483
what he does.

06:36.526 --> 06:38.963
And if I had,
would you have gone with him?

06:39.007 --> 06:41.183
- I guess not.

06:43.098 --> 06:45.100
Like pancakes?

06:46.841 --> 06:49.496
I don't know what your brother
promised, but, uh,

06:49.539 --> 06:52.150
we don't exactly have
a brunch menu.

06:52.194 --> 06:54.022
We've got a few snacks
in the back.

06:54.065 --> 06:57.417
- Just stay put.
I'll grab us something.

07:01.943 --> 07:03.248
The Purge put you
out of business

07:03.292 --> 07:05.207
since there's so little crime?

07:05.250 --> 07:08.863
- I don't know if that's really
how people work.

07:08.906 --> 07:12.562
I-I saw people break the law
for all sorts of reasons.

07:12.606 --> 07:16.000
Not usually the kind
you can save up for one night.

07:18.438 --> 07:21.266
- That's what they say.

07:21.310 --> 07:24.531
Till you've seen it up close.

07:24.574 --> 07:28.404
♪

07:28.448 --> 07:30.450
I lost my brother
on this night.

07:32.147 --> 07:35.672
A random Purger
sliced his head clean off.

07:37.413 --> 07:40.024
Said he just wanted
to watch it roll.

07:42.549 --> 07:44.681
- That's awful.

07:48.772 --> 07:52.733
Miguel and I?
We're OMF.

07:52.776 --> 07:56.301
When our parents died,
they sent us to a counselor.

07:56.345 --> 07:58.521
She tried to explain
how their sacrifice

07:58.565 --> 08:01.872
was going to help more people
than it would ever hurt.

08:01.916 --> 08:05.267
And we were so little,
I don't remember much of it.

08:05.310 --> 08:08.400
But I do remember
her saying that part.

08:08.444 --> 08:10.490
And it made me feel
a little better.

08:14.102 --> 08:15.886
- Hey, Pete,
check this out.

08:15.930 --> 08:17.409
- Okay.

08:17.453 --> 08:19.890
Excuse me.
- Yeah.

08:19.934 --> 08:26.941
♪

08:32.033 --> 08:35.515
- It must feel nice
to believe in something.

08:48.049 --> 08:50.268
- Room service.

08:50.312 --> 08:51.618
- Aha.

08:51.661 --> 08:54.098
- Wow, that actually
smells amazing.

08:54.142 --> 08:56.057
- Yeah, only took me
four tries.

08:59.190 --> 09:01.715
- Cheers.
Here's to starting over.

09:07.068 --> 09:09.940
- Well, no, I just...

09:09.984 --> 09:14.249
I think this night has...
taken a toll on all of us.

09:15.380 --> 09:19.384
And--and there was a lot riding
on that deal with your dad.

09:19.428 --> 09:22.692
And...I don't know.

09:25.303 --> 09:27.567
- Well, he's gone.

09:29.699 --> 09:32.659
But the company's still here,
and...

09:32.702 --> 09:36.619
I'm his only child, so I guess
whatever happens is...

09:36.663 --> 09:38.099
up to me.

09:38.142 --> 09:41.276
- Lila, we don't need to--
- I want to.

09:41.319 --> 09:43.583
I want to give you the deal.

09:46.150 --> 09:47.499
- Look, uh...

09:53.593 --> 09:55.638
This really isn't easy.

09:55.682 --> 09:58.249
Uh...

09:58.293 --> 10:01.644
part of me feels like

10:01.688 --> 10:05.343
Jenna and I should never have
even started down this road.

10:05.387 --> 10:07.781
I mean, we were just trying
to be something that we're not.

10:07.824 --> 10:09.913
- The project isn't just
your dream, Rick.

10:09.957 --> 10:12.829
It's hers too.

10:12.873 --> 10:15.615
I want to repair something
I had a hand in breaking.

10:15.658 --> 10:17.181
Please let me do that.

10:19.749 --> 10:21.795
- That's very generous of you.

10:21.838 --> 10:25.799
- So...

10:25.842 --> 10:27.931
Are we partners?

10:31.152 --> 10:34.677
Is it a yes or no?

10:34.721 --> 10:36.374
Do you still want the deal?

10:38.376 --> 10:41.031
- Honestly, Lila,

10:41.075 --> 10:43.817
I can't answer that.

10:43.860 --> 10:45.949
I need to talk it over
with Jenna.

10:48.865 --> 10:51.128
Oh, hey. I was, uh--

10:51.172 --> 10:52.564
I was just gonna
come check on you.

10:52.608 --> 10:55.655
I made you
a grilled cheese special.

10:56.743 --> 10:58.962
- Rick, can I have
a moment alone with Lila?

11:02.313 --> 11:03.663
Rick.

11:06.709 --> 11:09.320
- Yeah. Yeah, of course.
I'll, um--

11:09.364 --> 11:11.409
I should probably
check on the house again.

11:22.333 --> 11:25.119
- Hey.
- Stop, please.

11:28.905 --> 11:30.907
- I can't live in chaos.

11:32.648 --> 11:34.215
I can't do this anymore.

11:35.999 --> 11:37.914
- We're not doing anything.

11:37.958 --> 11:41.613
- Why did you offer Rick
that deal without me there?

11:41.657 --> 11:44.660
Maybe because you knew
I wouldn't take it?

11:44.704 --> 11:45.705
I wouldn't like it
if he did?

11:45.748 --> 11:49.143
Jen--
- Listen.

11:49.186 --> 11:52.668
You...sparked something in me.

11:52.712 --> 11:56.019
You...knocked me off-balance.

11:56.063 --> 11:57.760
In a good way.

11:57.804 --> 12:00.763
And I was selfish
for wanting more.

12:00.807 --> 12:04.419
But us, this,
whatever thing this is,

12:04.462 --> 12:06.073
it can't go on.

12:07.596 --> 12:09.163
I'm tired of all the games.

12:09.206 --> 12:10.947
- But you need someone
who can protect you.

12:10.991 --> 12:13.733
- No. No, I don't.
I can protect myself.

12:18.172 --> 12:20.391
He's manipulating you.

12:20.435 --> 12:23.133
When are you gonna stop
living his life?

12:24.831 --> 12:26.746
- No, it's just...

12:30.967 --> 12:32.969
We can be happy.

12:33.013 --> 12:35.145
You know that.
You've said that.

12:35.189 --> 12:37.147
- Oh, I've said a lot
of things that,

12:37.191 --> 12:38.975
yes, probably made
this harder for you.

12:39.019 --> 12:41.761
I know. I'm--

12:41.804 --> 12:43.675
I was confused.

12:45.373 --> 12:48.071
Lila, I want to be
clear with you.

12:48.115 --> 12:50.291
I know I haven't been
in the past.

12:51.988 --> 12:54.643
We're done.

12:54.686 --> 12:56.123
- No.

12:57.864 --> 13:00.170
That's bullshit.

13:00.214 --> 13:02.042
That's fucking bullshit.

13:02.085 --> 13:03.957
- I'm sorry.

13:04.000 --> 13:11.007
♪

13:16.665 --> 13:18.058
- Hey.

13:20.930 --> 13:23.759
Do you remember the first time
we took you to the stable?

13:25.761 --> 13:27.284
- Yeah.

13:27.328 --> 13:29.373
You didn't want to get
anywhere near those horses.

13:29.417 --> 13:31.288
You sat on the ground
with your arms crossed.

13:31.332 --> 13:33.987
You were like, "No way, Daddy,
I'm not going in there."

13:36.380 --> 13:37.947
You get that stubbornness
from me.

13:39.557 --> 13:40.863
I paid that trainer

13:40.907 --> 13:42.865
to cancel the rest
of her appointments

13:42.909 --> 13:45.955
because I was just gonna
wait you out

13:45.999 --> 13:48.262
for as long as it took.

13:48.305 --> 13:49.437
And it took
a pretty long time.

13:49.480 --> 13:51.482
It must've been five hours

13:51.526 --> 13:54.790
before you finally agreed
to saddle up.

13:54.834 --> 13:57.837
But you know what?

13:57.880 --> 13:59.882
- I loved it.

13:59.926 --> 14:03.407
Still do.
- And you excelled at it.

14:03.451 --> 14:06.497
Joy, true joy,

14:06.541 --> 14:09.022
comes from courage.

14:09.065 --> 14:11.154
So does greatness.

14:14.941 --> 14:17.073
There are some things
that you can only learn

14:17.117 --> 14:18.814
through experience.

14:18.858 --> 14:22.513
And the strength that you are
gonna gain from this today,

14:22.557 --> 14:24.646
there is literally nothing
that I can say

14:24.689 --> 14:27.562
that will make you understand

14:27.605 --> 14:29.477
what you're about to feel.

14:31.479 --> 14:33.176
- I want to be strong.

14:33.220 --> 14:34.699
- You are.

14:42.229 --> 14:44.013
- Yeah.

14:44.057 --> 14:45.493
- I was scared as hell.

14:45.536 --> 14:47.756
No.
- Of course!

14:47.799 --> 14:49.105
I agonized over it for weeks.

14:49.149 --> 14:50.890
I mean,
what kind of person wouldn't?

14:52.195 --> 14:54.937
But, sweetie,
that day came.

14:54.981 --> 14:58.332
And it was over,
just like that.

14:58.375 --> 15:01.291
And as soon as I'd done it,

15:01.335 --> 15:03.859
truly,
I knew it was right.

15:03.903 --> 15:09.169
♪

15:18.874 --> 15:20.180
- Coffee, please.

15:25.968 --> 15:28.797
You wandered off the bus
and got lost?

15:28.840 --> 15:31.887
- No.

15:31.931 --> 15:36.370
'Cause we could slip out back
and do the deed right now

15:36.413 --> 15:38.546
if you want.

15:38.589 --> 15:40.461
- Excuse me.

15:40.504 --> 15:44.117
- I Purged one of you
cult kids last year.

15:44.160 --> 15:46.206
Didn't put up a fight at all.

15:46.249 --> 15:48.034
At least not until
the very end.

15:48.077 --> 15:50.340
- Oh, you're such a badass,
what are you doing in here?

15:50.384 --> 15:51.776
Get out there, big man.

15:51.820 --> 15:54.257
Go out and slaughter
some kids.

15:54.301 --> 15:55.606
Go!

15:55.650 --> 15:57.565
- Hey!

16:02.962 --> 16:04.659
- You get one warning.

16:04.702 --> 16:07.270
'Cause I'm in a good mood.

16:07.314 --> 16:09.751
Don't bother my friends.
- Got it.

16:11.144 --> 16:12.710
Sorry.

16:15.539 --> 16:18.542
- That robe is attracting
the wrong kind of attention.

16:18.586 --> 16:20.066
I got a box full of clothes
in the back,

16:20.109 --> 16:21.371
if you wanna see
if something fits.

16:21.415 --> 16:23.025
- Sure.

16:23.983 --> 16:25.549
- Don't start shit in my bar.

16:29.205 --> 16:31.338
Hey.

16:41.783 --> 16:43.915
- Rick.
- No, hold on. Hold on.

16:47.745 --> 16:50.487
Stay--stay here
till I get back.

16:50.531 --> 16:51.662
Okay?

16:59.670 --> 17:06.677
♪

17:07.287 --> 17:08.766
Lila?

17:08.810 --> 17:12.727
♪

17:12.770 --> 17:13.902
Lila.

17:13.945 --> 17:20.952
♪

17:38.100 --> 17:40.494
- Do you want me to take that
outside and burn it?

17:43.366 --> 17:44.889
- Not a fan of your cult.

17:44.933 --> 17:46.848
- Tavis prefers the term
"new religion."

17:46.891 --> 17:49.068
I'm sure she does.

17:51.592 --> 17:53.463
- I know you think
it's bullshit.

17:53.507 --> 17:55.465
But you gotta understand,
I was all alone,

17:55.509 --> 17:57.119
no place to live,

17:57.163 --> 17:59.948
worrying about Miguel
halfway around the world.

17:59.991 --> 18:01.384
And Tavis was there for me

18:01.428 --> 18:03.299
when I needed something
to believe in.

18:05.388 --> 18:07.477
Did you meet Tavis in jail?

18:07.521 --> 18:09.131
- Kantrow rehab.

18:09.175 --> 18:12.047
My ex-boyfriend, he, um--

18:12.091 --> 18:14.136
I just--I got hooked
on some bad stuff.

18:14.180 --> 18:16.138
- She was your social worker.

18:16.182 --> 18:18.140
- That's her job.

18:19.402 --> 18:21.230
- Come in, Penelope.

18:25.321 --> 18:28.716
Tavis, uh, chooses
her members carefully,

18:28.759 --> 18:30.326
from what I gather.

18:30.370 --> 18:32.154
They have to be approved.

18:32.198 --> 18:34.809
- The NFFA.

18:34.852 --> 18:36.637
That's who's really
funding her.

18:36.680 --> 18:40.162
That's why she's
off-limits tonight.

18:40.206 --> 18:42.251
- No.
No, you've got it all wrong.

18:42.295 --> 18:43.774
It's not
a political organization.

18:43.818 --> 18:46.603
- Oh, sure,
that's what she says.

18:46.647 --> 18:48.431
It's all part
of the long con.

18:48.475 --> 18:50.607
Think about who she recruits.

18:50.651 --> 18:54.568
She trolls jails, hospitals,
homeless shelters.

18:54.611 --> 18:57.353
- To find people who need help,
who are looking for a purpose.

18:57.397 --> 19:01.227
- To find people the NFFA
has deemed disposable.

19:01.270 --> 19:03.533
Filling up the gas tank
on that blue bus

19:03.577 --> 19:05.709
is a hell of a lot cheaper
than socialized medicine.

19:06.884 --> 19:08.059
- You're lying.

19:08.103 --> 19:10.236
That's not possible.

19:10.279 --> 19:12.194
- When I was on the force,
we had proof:

19:12.238 --> 19:15.197
wire transfers, documents,
audition tapes.

19:15.241 --> 19:17.330
- They held auditions

19:17.373 --> 19:19.854
to find Tavis.

19:19.897 --> 19:22.030
She's just playing a part.

19:25.076 --> 19:27.644
♪

19:27.688 --> 19:29.951
- But I helped her
recruit people.

19:33.607 --> 19:35.043
- You didn't know.

19:35.086 --> 19:37.219
- I tried.

19:37.263 --> 19:39.221
My partner and I
were building a case,

19:39.265 --> 19:42.572
but the NFFA has cops
in its pockets too.

19:42.616 --> 19:44.792
The bosses squashed
the investigation.

19:44.835 --> 19:46.141
They destroyed the evidence.

19:46.185 --> 19:47.229
- Yeah, and now that bus
is full of kids

19:47.273 --> 19:48.578
just like I was--

19:48.622 --> 19:50.189
lost and afraid.

19:51.929 --> 19:53.322
I need to find that bus.

19:53.366 --> 19:55.106
- No, no.
Not the bus again.

19:55.150 --> 19:57.152
- I can't let my friends die
for nothing.

20:01.548 --> 20:08.555
♪

20:14.038 --> 20:21.045
♪

20:30.359 --> 20:31.404
- Jeez! Oh, my--
- Whoa, whoa, whoa!

20:31.447 --> 20:33.667
It's just me.
It's just me.

20:35.146 --> 20:37.845
- It wasn't, I swear.
I heard it too, okay?

20:37.888 --> 20:39.890
- Richard, Jenna!

20:39.934 --> 20:41.544
Are you home?
- Shit.

20:41.588 --> 20:42.850
Someone's at the door.

20:42.893 --> 20:44.721
Oh, fuck!

20:46.201 --> 20:47.811
Have you seen Ross?
- Oh, shit.

20:47.855 --> 20:49.857
- Richard, please,
I can't find Ross.

20:49.900 --> 20:51.206
Please tell me he's in there
with you.

20:51.250 --> 20:52.903
- Neighbor's wife.

20:52.947 --> 20:55.254
- Richard, Jenna!

20:55.297 --> 20:58.692
Where's Ross?
-Go home, Carol!

21:00.215 --> 21:02.086
- Uh, look, we'll talk
in the morning, okay?

21:02.130 --> 21:03.871
- No, no! Let me in!

21:03.914 --> 21:06.134
So you can finish
what Ross started?

21:06.177 --> 21:08.745
I--
- Carol, your husband is dead.

21:08.789 --> 21:10.312
- Lila, shut up.

21:10.356 --> 21:11.922
- What good is telling her that
gonna do?

21:11.966 --> 21:14.403
- Oh, my God.
- Carol, go home, please.

21:14.447 --> 21:17.058
- God, I told him that
you people were dangerous!

21:17.101 --> 21:19.539
-He attacked us!
- Open the door!

21:19.582 --> 21:21.541
- Your husband tried to shoot
a pregnant woman.

21:21.584 --> 21:23.107
He got what he deserved.
- Carol.

21:23.151 --> 21:24.413
- Leave!
- Carol!

21:24.457 --> 21:25.458
Listen to--Jesus, Carol.

21:25.501 --> 21:26.807
Someone's behind you.

21:26.850 --> 21:28.678
